	<strong><u>Company:</u></strong></p>
<p>
	Kenandy is a fast growing developer of native SaaS-based Social Enterprise application for manufacturing. Our Social Manufacturing application includes Inventory Management, Engineering, Supply Chain, Distribution Management, and Sales Order Processing, and the financial functions of AR, AP, GL, and financial reporting.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Kenandy is leading the way in the new world of manufacturing: manufacturing that is social, collaborative, and in the cloud. We are looking for smart, talented trailblazers looking for a growth opportunity who share our vision and passion for the next generation of social enterprise applications.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong><u>Basic Requirements:</u></strong>&nbsp; 2-5+ years experience developing&nbsp; Java, C++, Ruby, Force.com or Apex applications (Apex would be ideal).&nbsp; Understanding Apex classes, Triggers, S-controls, managed packaging will put your job application on the top of the pile. â˜º&nbsp; If you don&rsquo;t know Force.com, Visualforce, and Apex coding but are very smart, have loved coding since you were out of diapers, are a very quick learner and can &ldquo;wow&rdquo; us with your talent, please still apply.. you might get lucky!</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Requirements gathering, designing, coding, debugging, performance analysis, packaging and deployment of customer real-life business application on the Force.com platform, Salesforce.com&rsquo;s enterprise cloud computing platform.&nbsp;&nbsp; (Kenandy Social Manufacturing products run the core business processes of companies from order entry through manufacturing to financial reporting.&nbsp; Our products are the backbone to how companies produce and manage their product operations.)&nbsp;</li>
	<li>
		Work directly with customers to define requirements</li>
	<li>
		Work with many departments within Kenandy including support, consulting, product management , and engineering</li>
	<li>
		Involves working as a member of a project team building new functionality and enhancing existing functionality.&nbsp; Design and deploy high quality, scalable code often working directly with end user.&nbsp;</li>
	<li>
		Some occasional offsite customer meetings or visits</li>
	<li>
		Design and develop integrations between Kenandy applications and other systems as may be required by customers</li>
	<li>
		Assist with training members of Kenandy development teams, sales, and customers</li>
	<li>
		Ensure that documentation of application code, as well as application use and flow, is accurate and well written.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong><u>Full Requirements:</u></strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		BA/BS in Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, or similar technical degree or equivalent experience</li>
	<li>
		2-5+ years experience in developing&nbsp; Java, Ruby,&nbsp;C++, Force.com, Visualforce, and or Apex applications (Apex would be ideal).&nbsp; Understanding of Apex classes, Triggers, S-controls, managed packaging</li>
	<li>
		Great interpersonal and English language skills to work with many different groups within Kenandy as well as with customers directly;&nbsp; an A++ programmer without strong communication skills is not a good fit.</li>
	<li>
		Disciplined self-starter,&nbsp; good at finding solutions to problems without explicit directions</li>
	<li>
		Able to be highly productive both working alone and in close collaboration within a team</li>
	<li>
		Ability to multi process and thrive in a fast-paced, customer driven,&nbsp; sometimes unpredictable but always fun and energized environment</li>
	<li>
		Knowledgeable and passionate about exploring and experimenting with the latest application development technologies</li>
	<li>
		Must fully understand the process of developing customer facing applications including cloud based APIs and protocols</li>
	<li>
		Proficiency in object oriented programming</li>
	<li>
		Knowledge of Agile methodology is an advantage</li>
	<li>
